My fandom name is Beachy, and this is a multi-fandom blog. 
I'm also a multi-shipper. It's likely I do not sail your ship, but I don't wank and expect visitors to play nicely as well. That includes not adding hate or negativity to my posts, altering them to suit your own ships, or removing my original comments. If you do, you will be blocked.
IRL they call me Doctor. Yep, I'm that old. Sometimes I write things that other people watch. It's all good! I like mocha latte with bourbon. A lot.

summary: Quotes from 'David Tennant Does a Podcast With Jodie Whittaker' that deserve repeating.
body:
Quotes from ‘David Tennant Does a Podcast With Jodie Whittaker’ that deserve repeating.

Seeing as Jodie did an amazing job of talking all these are her quotes with a few additional D.T ones at the end.

- “Eventually I will just kind of randomly go off on tangents of making shit up”

- “You were a cat with nine lives and so the first life put everything into when you’ve got the most amount of energy”

- “How are you going to know if you don’t ask?”

- “Peope are always like you’re a tomboy, I’m not, I’m just myself”

- *To D.T* “There’s no way you were a curvy kid”

- “I talk so much I think that it’s not to my detriment but I sometimes struggle with the line of when to overshare”

- “Awks”

- “My lovely little deep frown line has made it onto all the posters, I’ve got an angry bum”

- “Maybe theses things will be a thing of the past and we’ll finally accept that we’re all different and that is ace”

- “I got asked to get my tash waxed, didn’t know I had one”

- “You’re always The Doctor”

- “Wanting to be a successful actor and wanting to be famous are two separate dreams and I only had one of those dreams”

- “There’s loads of stuff that I just think are mine and should be mine and I don’t understand why I should have to explain what belongs to me and what doesn’t”

- “As an actor I can’t sit there and complain about representation if you’re not going to play the dream role that you would have had as a kid”

- “The conversation is let’s open up points of view and to not always tell the same story from the same perspective. That is the conversation. Isn’t it interesting to see the world through many different eyes”

- “I also don’t think my opinion is law, it’s an opinion”

- “We are all still very flawed characters and that is okay”

- “Young people should have many different types of people to look up to and none of that should be perfection”

- “Too many people out there thinking their opinion is fact”

- “I was baseball capped up coz it were week after the announcement thinking I’m some kind of celeb. Sunglasses inside and all that shit”

- “I can’t remember the question before I started insulting ya”

- “You’re not coming in and playing The Doctor, you are playing the truth of the scene and The Doctor will come out of that”

- “There wasn’t a huge gobbledygook scene”

- On trying to understand the rules of Dr Who “I were getting so stressed about it and okay, she’s my wife but what does this mean?”

- “No traits really of The Doctor are gender specific I don’t think”

- “The two hearts give us quite a lot of breadth for emotion”

- “I never met Billie but I thought she were ace”

- “There was just something maybe about my accent that I just presumed they wouldn’t want it”

- “It were ace going round the room and I went 'I’m Jodie Whittaker and I play THE DOCTOR’ like really played it cool”

- About Bradley, Mandip and Tosin “But having three people that never let you get above your station, there’s no egos, so sometimes it would be 'Oh fucking hell, Shut up ya grumpy twat’ you could just speak to them however you want”

- “Bradley, he’s just like a big kid on set”

- “Mandip is just the loveliest, she couldn’t be more even, never in a bad mood she’s just always like happy, she’s just a good person”

- “Tosin’s absolutally hilarious because he’s just so laid back and then you know he’s just always having napps like some sorta teenager but he’s a brilliant story teller”

D.T quotes

- “I’ve been much cooler since I started having black coffee”

- “That makes me feel very smug expect when I’d finished the bowl Georga then said 'You know that yogurt is two weeks out of date”

- *In a very overall Yorkshire accent* “What like in’t Skelmanthorpe?”

body:
I didn’t thought I could love Jodie Whittaker even more but..

..DTs podcast with her was just amazing

Here are some of my favorite moments:

  • She would be running a damn pub uff
  • „[…] How are you gonna know if you don‘t ask?“
  • „I was brought up totally genderneutral“
  • „Have you heard of doctor who?“
  • „YeAh ThAt‘D Be LoVeLy“ her voice is so cute ahh
  • „This is for life“
  • I love the way she said „oh fuck yeah“
  • Imagine 13 without her accent :(
  • „Mandip is just the lovely.. -she she couldn‘t be more even. She [is] never in a bad mood. She is always.. like.. happy. She [is] just a good person“ I wan‘t a friendship like this :‘)
  • „He [Tosin] is always havin‘ naps“ I‘m tosin…
  • „Thanks DT“

david Tennant does a podcast with ep 3
summary: My thoughts about the podcast ep: When David talked about how the headphones make people sound sexier than they actually are and...
body:
My thoughts about the podcast ep:

  • When David talked about how the headphones make people sound sexier than they actually are and Jodie was like “I don’t think it works for you, David” HER VOICE WAS LITerALLY so sexy… And I say that as a person who hates calling anyone sexy
  • David eating yoghurt that was a week out of date was kinda hilarious
  • I have never noticed Jodie’s frown line, but now it’s kinda hard to ignore. Not that it makes her any less attractive
  • I kinda wanna try almond milk now. Even though I have this feeling that I am going to hate it
  • Jodie being a people person is so not surprising
  • Jodie does like to talk a lot (Not complaining… yet xD)
  • I really wanna be one of those people Jodie overshares with
  • I really wanna meet Jodie (but also I don’t bc I think I would be really awkward and then I could never watch anything with her in it ever again)
  • I am super glad it was Jodie and not Ben Wishaw, but I did have to laugh when she talked about that story. (Like really you get the chance to speak to the new Doctor, who is amazing and the best there has been so far and all you say is “I really wanted Ben Wishaw”?)
  • People do need to remember that actors are just people too and that they deserve to have privacy and that they are allowed to be like “that is private and I want it to remain so”
  • I love that Jodie and Olivia both just call him DT
  • it was way too short
  • Jodie seems like such a warm and lovely person
  • I wish I was even half as confident as Jodie

Jodie Whittaker: “NO not nothing!” Don’t throw me under the bus! Look at you trying to be the favorite Doctor again” 
[she goes on a story about being recognized the first time after the news]
“…I can’t remember the question before I started insulting you”

body:
TCA 19: Britbox series ‘There She Goes’ explores the life of a family with a severely learning disabled child

There She Goesis a dramedy about a British family and their trials and tribulations while raising a 9-year-old daughter with a severe learning disability. Based on the real story of creator Shaun Pye’s own family, and his daughter Joey, the series takes a realistic and unapologetic look at the life of this family, their love and frustrations.
